datum <-  c(1.78, 1.86, 1.96, 2, 2, 1.96, 1.72, 1.64, 1.74, 1.7, 1.82, 1.82, 1.9, 1.82, 2.08)

1 Pseudo Data Dot Plot

stripchart(x, method = "overplot", jitter = 0.1, offset = 1/3, vertical = FALSE, group.names, add = FALSE, at = NULL, xlim = NULL, ylim = NULL, ylab = NULL, xlab = NULL, dlab = "", glab = "",log = "", pch = 0, col = par("fg"), cex = par("cex"), axes = TRUE, frame.plot = axes, ...)

** method= overplot, stack, jitter

#par(mfrow=c(1,2))
stripchart(datum, main = "Pseudo Dot Plot")

#grid.table(datum)
stripchart(airquality$Ozone)

stripchart(datum, pch = 19, main = "Dot Plot", xlim = range(pretty(datum))) # ?pretty

1.1 Stacked dot plot

stripchart(datum, pch = 19, main = "Pseudo Stacked Dot Plot", method = "stack", xlim = range(pretty(datum))) 

stripchart(airquality$Ozone, pch = 19, method = "stack")

1.2 Jittered dot plot

stripchart(datum, pch = 19, main = "Pseudo Jittered Dot Chart", method = "jitter", jitter = 0.5)

stripchart(airquality$Ozone, main = "Jittered Dot Chart",  xlab = "Parts Per Billion",
   ylab = "Ozone", method = "jitter", pch = 19)

1.3 Grouped dot plot

stripchart(datum[datum.groups=="A"], pch = 1, method = "stack", main = "Grouped Dot Plot", xlim = range(pretty(datum)), col = "blue")
stripchart(datum[datum.groups=="B"],pch = 2, method = "stack", add = T, col = "red")
stripchart(datum[datum.groups=="C"],pch = 3, method = "stack", add = T, col = "green")

1.4 Multiple and vertical dot plot

** 1**

stripchart(Ozone ~ Month, data = airquality, ylab = "dose", pch = 19, frame = FALSE)

** 2**

stripchart(Ozone ~ Month, data = airquality, pch = 19, frame = FALSE, vertical = TRUE, method = "jitter")

** 3**

temp <- airquality$Temp
temp_norm <- rnorm(200, mean = mean(temp, na.rm = TRUE), sd = sd(temp, na.rm = TRUE)) # gererate normal distribution with same mean and sd
x <- list("temp" = temp, "norm" = temp_norm) # make a list
stripchart(x, main = "Multiple stripchart for comparision", xlab = "Degree Fahrenheit", ylab = "Temperature", method= "jitter", col = c("orange","red"), pch = 16)

** 4**

stripchart(Temp ~ Month, data = airquality, main = "Different strip chart for each month", xlab = "Months", ylab = "Temperature", col = "brown3", group.names = c("May","June","July","August","September"),
           vertical = TRUE, pch = 16)

a<-rnorm(1000,100,10)
a<-as.integer(a)
stripchart(a, method = "stack", at= c(0.05), pch=20, cex=1, las=1, frame.plot = F, xlim=c(60,150), main= "balk")

3 ggplot2 package

http://www.sthda.com/english/wiki/ggplot2-stripchart-jitter-quick-start-guide-r-software-and-data-visualization

library(ggplot2)
data("ToothGrowth")
d2<-ToothGrowth
p <- ggplot(d2,aes(x = dose, y = len)) 
p + geom_jitter() # add jitter

p + geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0.2)) # Change the position, 0.2 degree of jitter in x direction

p + geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0.1))

p + geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0))

p <- p + geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0.1))
p + coord_flip() # rotate stripthart

p + scale_x_discrete(limits = c("0.5", "2")) # Choose which items to display

# Change point size
p<- ggplot(d2,aes(x = dose, y = len)) 
p + geom_jitter(position=position_jitter(0.2), cex = 1.2)

# Change shape
p + geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0.2), shape = 17)

# stripchart with mean points
p + stat_summary(fun.y = mean, geom = "point", shape = 18, size = 3, color = "red")
## Warning: `fun.y` is deprecated. Use `fun` instead.

# stripchart with median points
p + stat_summary(fun.y = median, geom = "point", shape = 18, size = 3, color = "red")
## Warning: `fun.y` is deprecated. Use `fun` instead.

# Add basic box plot
p + geom_boxplot()+ geom_jitter(position=position_jitter(0.2)) # hata
# Add notched box plot
p + geom_boxplot(notch = TRUE)+ geom_jitter(position=position_jitter(0.2))
# Add violin plot
p + geom_violin(trim = FALSE)+ geom_jitter(position=position_jitter(0.2))

p <- ggplot(d2, aes(x = dose, y = len)) + geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0.2))
p + stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_sdl", mult = 1, geom = "crossbar", width = 0.5)
p + stat_summary(fun.data = mean_sdl, mult = 1, geom = "pointrange", color = "red")
# Change point shapes by groups
p<-ggplot(d2, aes(x = dose, y = len, shape = dose)) + 
    geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0.2))
p
# Change point shapes manually
p + scale_shape_manual(values = c(1,17,19))
